		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Really liked this lesson, unfortunately I will have to come back to it in the future as I am nursing a PIP injury (hyperextended playing rythym guitar) on my fretting hand ring finger. Proper technique as noted in the video is important because you can really hurt yourself and if your finger is hurting (like mine) best to keep it cool. My doctor has told me to lay off for a month or so to avoid a full ligament tear/rupture and surgery&#8230; Currently relegated to the Danny Mo index finger technique&#8230;</p>
